From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ArcBoost Builder <build@arcboost.local>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 22:43:44 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 11/13] ArcBoost: route circular_feature to
 BinMapper::InitAsCircular at Dataset construction
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Closes the gap between 'config.circular_feature is parsed' and 'features
listed in circular_feature actually get BinType::CircularBin'.

Adds:
  - DatasetLoader::circular_features_ set, populated from config_.circular_feature
    using the same name:/index syntax as categorical_feature (with a clear
    fatal if a feature is listed in both).
  - In ConstructFromSampleData and ConstructFromMultipleData, branch on
    circular_features_ alongside categorical_features_ to set bin_type =
    BinType::CircularBin and route through BinMapper::InitAsCircular()
    instead of FindBin().
  - BinMapper::InitAsCircular(num_bin, period, missing_type) implementation
    in src/io/bin.cpp — sets bin_type_, num_bin_, circular_period_,
    missing_type_, default_bin_, most_freq_bin_, is_trivial_, min_val_,
    max_val_, and clears the categorical / numeric-specific bookkeeping.

After this patch, 'circular_feature="0"' in the params dict actually marks
column 0 as circular and the dispatch in feature_histogram.hpp routes it to
FindBestThresholdCircular (still a stub until the algorithmic patch lands).
